                                    &#160;</div></ulink></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><para>In this way, we divide a whole bibliographical entry into three parts: </para><ul><li>The core Publication data. In the case of a book, this may be all the information one can supply, if the book does not occur as part of a
                series. </li><li>The publication Container. In the case of a book, the publication container is typically a book series.</li><li>The Location of the publication inside the container. In the case of a book, this is the identification of where inside the series the
                publication occurs, that is, its volume number.</li></ul><para>We shall see that this way of disposing a bibliographical entry applies equally to publications inside periodicals and anthologies. </para></chapter></book>